review_blob: Mrk cola gjennomsiktig medium beige skum. Bygg aroma alkohol. Balansert fettshiiiut ja
Bitch black beige medium. Stlig lakris, kaffe aroma. Crazy kaffesmak, bitter ettersmak. Holy shit....
Hazy Orange lett pale ale ikke s my bitterhet balansert fin. Kjekk p starten av en helaften foffern sei hei

50 cl bottle from vinmonopolet Valkendorfsgate, Bergen. Pours hazy golden orange with a medium white head. Aroma: Fruity feast! Blackcurrant, apricot and belgian yeast. Taste mellow at first with the fruids before a awesome dry aftertaste of belguim arrives. Nice (=

0,5 Bottle. Pours black with a small beige head. Aroma: Smoky aroma, dark malts, juniper. Lots of taste: smooth in the start with wild berries and roasty malt, ends up quite bitter and dry with a aftertaste of jiniper. Medium carbonation. Awesome stuff =)
Pours black with a creamy beige head. Aroma: sweet malt, hay cofee. Taste: dry, black malt. Decent 4,7 stout.

Got the 0,25L bottle from a beer shop in Riga. Pours clear red-brown with a small white head. Aroma: Sour yeast, Hardanger apples, citrus. Taste: Sweet and fruity in the beginning with hints of grape and lots of sugar. Sour in the end. I enjoyed this lambic!
Pours dark armber with a small off-white head. Aroma: citrus, anise. Taste more or less the same. Medium body with lots of carbonation. This one was in my backlog for too long!
Half pint p henrik... Ser passe amber ut med lite hvitt skum, klar. Aroma: massiv humle. Smak: trr i munn med mye humle, relativt lett l. Bitter ettersmak med litt anis. Bra saker!
Pours dark brown, creamy head. Aroma characterized by nuts and anise. Taste is lovely sweet with a well carbonated body. Its most def silky!

beer_brewer_name: Schneider Weisse G. Schneider & Sohn GmbH
review_blob: Pours caramel with a small head. Aroma characterized by banana, sweetness and wheat. High carbonation. Tastes banana, wheat and alcohol.
beer_name: Schneider Weisse Tap X Mein Nelson Sauvin

review_blob: Pitch black with a bubbly beige head. Roasted coffee with licorice. Taste hops, alcohol, coffee and licorice. Very enjoyable.
Bottle. Hop explosion! Pours hazy amber with a big creamy head. Aroma dominated by complex hoppyness and sweet malts. Tasted the same. Smooth!

This imperial brown ale has been one of my favourites for some years. "Slepytt"-appearance. The aroma is characterized by coffee and licorice. Tastes the same + caramel, hops and special malts. Sparkely.
I think this one is a classic! Its just so fresh and smooth! Pours hazy orange with a big white head. Hoppy aroma. Taste is balanced nicely between malts and citrus.
From a can. Hazelnut brown with a creamy white head. The aroma is really weak, hints of caramell taste the same. Watery..
Bottle. Pours lively with lots of carbonation, floaters all over! A nice spicy "belgian" aroma. A well balanced taste. Sweet but very nice.
40cl on tap. Clear and golden with a white medium head. Medium bitter. Not the worst pilsner ever.
50cl on tap. Beautiful pitch black with a creamy beige head. Taste roasted meat. Dry.
35,5cl bottle. Smells vanilla. Taste coffe, water and alcohol. Lively carbonation. Dry medium body.
50cl. Shared with friends. Pours pitch brown with a medium light beige head. Smells sweet coffee with a hint of vanilla. Light body. A little dry. Decent price..
Batch 773.  50cl bottle. Hazy and amber appearance. Smells peach and citrus. Taste hop, pine and spurce. Excelent balance, not as bitter as i assumed this double IPA would be. But great!

50cl on tap. Awesome porter, all black with a beautiful light-brown head. It smelled roasted coffee and dark chocolate, there where also some hints of licorice. The taste was more or less the same. Full bodyed, dry, soft carbonation. I would recommend it!
beer_name: Dark Horse Reserve Special Black Ale

review_blob: 65cl bottle shared with two friends, a whole bottle is too much! Pitch black with a thin light brown head. It really smells like creme brulee. After a while you could smell the alcohol also. The taste is super sweet, like caramel and vanilla with a roasty after-taste. A nice dessert in small portions..
beer_name: Southern Tier Blackwater Series: Creme Brulee Stout
